<br>
This is a 66 card deck of Uruk Savagry!<br>
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">A normal choke deck always goes second, making sure you walk along your own sites, ensuring a choke. With this said, its best to bid at about 4 and go second (bid any more and you risk Enquea killing Boromir).<br>
What you want to do is get your rangers loaded with No Strangers and Armor (they live longer!). The Hobbits naturally get their swords and can hide up until site 5. With A Talent out, it should be pretty hard for your opponant to get out some nastys on you. Walking one site at a time is generally smart to do , but sometimes you can risk a double-move. If things get hairy, Boromir is a god and can take on a Cave Troll, provided he has an Armor. Combined with Elendil&#39;s Valor, he becomes a formidible fighting force. Don&#39;t forget that Aragorn will heal everyone except Frodo, making sure Merry and Boromir survive the next round. When everyone is equiped with their proper gear, there is little your opponant can do to hurt you. Blade Tips could be a problem but Athelas and Aragorn&#39;s healing kind of negates that. A swarm could hurt you but with P.A.T.H.S. , what can they do?<br>
The Uruks are just plain ungodly! Big Beef combined with the Spies definatley ensure a beatdown on somebody. Archery could be a problem for ANYBODY but there are 3 Spies and the site 7 should spare you from Legolas and Aragorn. But, you might ask, where are the Snows? Well, this deck relies on a lot of Uruk-pump so they unfortunatly didn&#39;t make the cut. With huge solid Uruks, the Free Peoples don&#39;t stand too much of a chance. The Goblin Runners are great in getting your guys out faster (especially when Uruks roam all the way to the Bridge, but hopefully Hollen will fix that) and if you can pull of an Uruk-swarm, you&#39;re golden. <br>
Well, thats about it. If you don&#39;t like Uruks, Saruman will strike down upon thee with GREAT VENGEANCE and FURIOUS ANGER and you will know that Saruman is the lord when he lays his vengeance upon thee!<br>
<br>
